===Etymology 1===
* First attested in 1677.
* From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|abrādō||lang=la||scrape off|lang=la}}, from {{term|ab||from, away from|lang=la}} + {{m|la|rādō||scrape}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|abrad|ing}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[rub off|rub]] or [[wear off]]; [[erode]]. {{defdate|First attested in the late 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=7}}</ref>
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To wear down or exhaust, as a person; [[irritate]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To irritate by rubbing; [[chafe]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To cause the surface to become more rough.
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To undergo [[abrasion]].

